  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the oats, dice or grate the apple, then add ½ the apple to a clean mixing bowl along with the remaining oats ingredients. Whisk together until well combined. Divide the mixture between containers, about 130g per container. Make sure your butter is fridge-cold."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the yoghurt topping, add the yoghurt to a clean mixing bowl with the remaining topping ingredients. Whisk vigorously for about 2 mins until the mixture becomes shinny and slightly aerated. Add the remaining grated/diced apple and mix through. Gently spoon the mixture over the oats, about 100g per container. I spoon the yoghurt around the edge of the container first before adding to the middle to maintain a visual line between the oats and the topping, but that’s just aesthetic."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the crumble, add all the ingredients into a clean bowl. Using your fingers, mix the ingredients together until you have no lumps of butter and a nice crumbly texture. Sprinkle over the top of each container."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cover and place in the fridge overnight. The oats will keep for 3 days."
    }
  ],
